The paper discusses low complexity decoding algorithms for product codes, which are commonly used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions fiber-optic communications, which suggests that it could belong to cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The algorithms proposed in the paper are iterative, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Information Theory).
